there was a little girl who lived in a village near the forest.  She was a good little girl, who always went about things in the right way; but she was very fond of going out into the fields and playing with and talking to the flowers and the little birds.  Now and then she would take a little cake out of her pocket, and give it to a poor little man who was collecting sticks for fire-wood.  She was always very kind to him, and the old
